"record\">{{cite web|title=Partial record|url=http://www.muaythaitv.com/fighters/diesellek-topkingboxing-f4405.html|website=Muaythaitv}}</ref>\n\n== Lethwei record ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\"  style=\"width:100%; clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; font-size:85%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:darkGrey;\"| <span style=\"color:white;\">Professional Lethwei record</span>\n|- valign=\"top\"\n|<div class=\"NavFrame\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"background:white; \"><span style=\"color:black;\">'''0 wins (0 (T)KOs), 1 losses, 0 draws'''</span></div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:left; display:collapse;\">\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|- align=\"center\" bgcolor=\"#FFBBBB\"\n| 2018-08-19 || Loss ||align=left|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[Dave Leduc]] || 2018 Myanmar Lethwei World Championship || [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]] || KO || 1 || 2:23\n|-\n! style=background:white colspan=9 |{{small| The bout was for the Openweight Myanmar Lethwei World Championship Title}}\n|}</div></div>\n'''''Legend''''': {{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win |border=1px solid #CCFFCC}}\n{{legend2|#FFBBBB|Loss |border=1px solid #FFBBBB}}\n{{legend2|#c5d2ea|Draw/No contest |border=1px solid #c5d2ea}}\n{{legend2|White|Notes |border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of male kickboxers]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Diesellek TopkingBoxing}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Lightweight kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Muay Thai trainers]]\n[[Category:Welterweight kickboxers]]\n[[Category:Thai male Muay Thai practitioners]]\n[[Category:People from Surin Province]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Thai Muay Thai fighter}}\n{{Infobox martial artist\n| name            = Diesellek TopkingBoxing\n| native_name     = \n| image           = \n| image_size      = \n| caption         = \n| birth_name      = \n| other_names     = Diesellek Rungruangyon <br /> Diesellek Soot Raaeng Geert <br /> Diesellek Seepongsert Sanong\n| nationality     = [[Thailand|Thai]]\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1985|5|9}}\n| birth_place     = [[Kalasin Province|Kalasin]], [[Isan]], [[Thailand]]\n| fighting_out_of = [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]]\n| height          = {{height|m=1.74|precision=1}}\n| weight          = {{convert|75|kg|lb st|abbr=on}}\n| weight_class    = [[Welterweight]] <br /> [[Middleweight]] \n| style           = [[Muay Thai]]\n| stance          = Orthodox\n| team            = Galaxy Gym\n| trainer         = \n| years_active    = \n| kickbox_loss    = \n| kickbox_win     = \n| kickbox_kowin   =\n| kickbox_draw    = \n| kickbox_nc      = \n| other           = \n| occupation      = \n| spouse          = \n| relatives       = \n| students        = \n| university      =\n| url             = \n| boxrec          =\n| sherdog         =\n| education       = \n| updated         = \n}}\n\n'''Diesellek TopkingBoxing''' (born May 9, 1985) is a [[Thailand|Thai]] [[middleweight]] [[Muay Thai]] fighter.<ref name=\"Topkingboxing\">{{cite web|last1=Raja|first1=Romain|title=Raphael LLODRA vs DIESELLEK en main event du ONE VS ONE|url=http://muaythaitv.fr/news/raphael-llodra-vs-diesellek-en-main-event-du-one-vs-one-n3864.html#sthash.RJa0OnYq.dpbs|website=Muaythaitv.Fr|date=12 March 2014}}</ref> He is a former [[Rajadamnern Stadium]], [[World Professional Muaythai Federation|WPMF]], [[International Kickboxing Federation|IKF]] Champion.<ref name=\"Siamfightmag\">{{cite web|last1=Trefeu|first1=Serge|title=Interview with Diesellek TopkingBoxing|url=http://www.siamfightmag.com/fr/muaythai-fr/interviews-fr/boxeursthailandais-fr/634-diesellek-top-king-boxing|website=Siam Fight Mag|date=4 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n== Early career ==\nBorn in [[Kalasin Province|Kalasin]], near [[Roi Et Province|Roi Et]], Thailand. Diessellek started fighting at the age of eleven. At the age of 15, he joined the Top King Boxing gym in Samutsakorn, 30 km south of [[Bangkok]].<ref name=\"Siamfightmag\" />\n\n== Career ==\n=== Muaythai ===\n\nOn 31 January, 2015, won by decision against [[Samy Sana]] in [[Nancy, France]].<ref name=\"Samy Sana win\">{{cite web|title=DIESELLEK SOOT RAAENG GEERT WINS|url=https://www.thaiboxingsydney.com/diesellek-soot-raaeng-geert-wins/|website=ThaiBoxing Sydney|date=2 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 March, 2012, Diesellek knocked out current [[Lumpini Stadium]] and [[Rajadamnern Stadium]] champion [[:fr:Youssef Boughanem|Youssef Boughanem]]<ref name=\"Siam fight mag\">{{cite web|last=Trefeu|first=Serge|title=Interview with Youssef Boughanem|url=https://www.siamfightmag.com/en/muaythai-en/interviews-muaythai-en/foreign-boxers-en/598-youssef-boughanem-belgium|website=Siam Fight Mag|date=5 January 2012}}</ref> with his left kick at Lumpini Stadium.<ref name=\"Fight Sports Asia\">{{cite web|last1=Fletcher|first1=Daniel|title=Diesel lek Top King Boxing vs. Youssef Kiatpetch Gym|url=https://fightsportasia.wordpress.com/2012/04/01/diesel-lek-vs-youssef-kiatpetch|website=Fight Sports Asia|date=1 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 June, 2008, Diesellek wins [[International Kickboxing Federation|IKF World Title]] against [[Marco Piqu\u00e9]] in [[Montego Bay, Jamaica]].<ref name=\"Siam fight mag 3\">{{cite web|last=Trefeu|first=Serge|title=The Galaxy Gym|url=http://www.siamfightmag.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=607:the-galaxy-gym&catid=58:a-la-une-en&Itemid=263&lang=en|website=Siam Fight Mag|date=8 January 2012}}</ref> The IKF stripped him of the title on September 15th, 2017 due to inactivity.<ref name=\"Past IKF Champs\">{{cite web |author= IKF Team |title=Past PRO Champs|url= https://www.ikfkickboxing.com/PastProChampions.htm|website=IKF}}</ref>\n\n=== Lethwei ===\nOn 19 August, 2018, at the occasion of the 3rd MLWC, Diesellek faced [[Dave Leduc]]<ref name=\"Pre fight Weekly fight\">{{cite web|title=\u524d\u65e5\u8a08\u91cf\u3001\u8a18\u8005\u4f1a\u898b\u7d42\u4e86\uff01\u7b2c4\u56de\u30df\u30e3\u30f3\u30de\u30fc\u30fb\u30e9\u30a6\u30a7\u30a4\u30fb\u30ef\u30fc\u30eb\u30c9\u30fb\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30d4\u30aa\u30f3\u30b7\u30c3\u30d7\uff08MLWC-4\uff09\u30df\u30e3\u30f3\u30de\u30fc\u30fb\u30e4\u30f3\u30b4\u30f3\u5927\u4f1a|url=https://miruhon.net/103961|website=The Weekly Fight|date=18 August 2018}}</ref> inside the Thein Pyu Stadium in [[Yangon]], [[Myanmar]].<ref name=\"Fox Asia preflight\">{{cite web|last1=Arthur|first1=Richard|title=Dave Leduc to defend Golden Belt at Lethwei World Championship 2018|url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/combat-sports/929398/dave-leduc-to-defend-golden-belt-at-lethwei-world-championship-2018/|website=FOX Sports Asia|date=18 August 2018}}</ref> The matchup was mediatized as ''Lethwei vs Muaythai''. Leduc won by KO at 2:23 of the first round.<ref name=\"MTA MLWC 3\">{{cite web |author= MTA Team |title=The Most Terrifying Man in Combat Sports Returned Last Night |url= https://muaythaiauthority.com/watch-the-most-terrifying-man-in-combat-sports-returned-last-night|website=Muaythai Authority|date=19 August 2018}}</ref> \n\n== Titles and achievements ==\n* '''[[World Professional Muaythai Federation]]'''\n** WPMF World Title\n* '''[[International Kickboxing Federation]]'''\n** IKF Light Middleweight World Champion<ref name=\"Past IKF Champs\" />\n* [[Rajadamnern Stadium]] (154&nbsp;lbs) Champion\n\n== Muay Thai record ==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" width=100% style=\"clear:both; margin:1.5em auto; font-size:85%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 style=\"background:#A9A9A9\" | <span style=\"color:white;\">Kickboxing record</span>\n|- valign=\"top\" \n|<div class=\"NavFrame\">\n<div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"background:white; \"><span style=\"color:black;\">''' 125 Wins ''', '''32 Losses''', '''3 Draw'''</span></div>\n<div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"text-align:left; display:collapse;\">\n{|class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n|- align=\"center\"  bgcolor=\"#dddddd\"\n| '''Date''' || '''Result''' || '''Opponent''' || '''Event''' || '''Location''' || '''Method''' || '''Round''' || '''Time'