st Virginia]]: Confirmed its first case; it was the last US state to do so.<ref name=\"Mar17_WV\">{{Cite news |url=https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/west-virginia-the-last-us-state-without-coronavirus-confirms-1st-case/ |title=West Virginia, the last US state without coronavirus, confirms 1st case |access-date=March 17, 2020 |agency=Associated Press |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317224314/https://myfox8.com/news/coronavirus/west-virginia-the-last-us-state-without-coronavirus-confirms-1st-case/ |archive-date=March 17, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==== March 18 ====\n* Florida: U.S. congressman [[Mario D\u00edaz-Balart]] is one of the first members of Congress to be tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|title=Reps. Mario Diaz-Balart and Ben McAdams become first members of Congress to test positive for coronavirus|first=Paul|last=Leblanc|date=March 18, 2020|website=cnn.com|access-date=March 21, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321105409/https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/18/politics/mario-diaz-balart-coronavirus/index.html|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Thousands of spring-breakers flock to Florida beaches despite warnings about keeping social distance. The [[Clearwater, Florida|Clearwater City Council]] voted to close down [[Clearwater Beach]] for two weeks, starting March 23 at 6 a.m. The coronavirus has infected 328 Florida residents and visitors.<ref>[https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html Thousands flock to Florida beaches, ignoring coronavirus concerns] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320221138/https://news.yahoo.com/thousands-flock-florida-beaches-ignoring-060744453.html |date=March 20, 2020 }} by Sophie Lewis, CBS New, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Kentucky: The wife of [[List of mayors of Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville mayor]] [[Greg Fischer]] tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/metro-government/2020/03/18/louisville-mayor-greg-fischers-wife-tests-positive-covid-19/2869369001/|title=Louisville Mayor Greg Fischer's wife tests positive for coronavirus, will self-isolate|first=Darcy|last=Costello|website=The Courier-Journal|accessdate=Mar 19, 2020}}</ref>\n*Louisiana: Rev. Tony Spell of Life Tabernacle Church in [[East Baton Rouge Parish]] hosts hundreds at a church service in open defiance of Governor [[John Bel Edwards|John Bel Edwards']] (D) ban against gatherings of more than 50 people.<ref>[https://thehill.com/policy/healthcare/488318-louisiana-church-defies-coronavirus-recommendations-to-hold-service-for-300?fbclid=IwAR3Fy0WDhtRR-_dCFyYFj1nXwqMw1aeImfznyKF5NlxAGjGEZSsIeQjcYXo Louisiana church defies coronavirus recommendations to hold service for 300] BY ZACK BUDRYK, The Hill, 18 Mar 2020</ref>\n* Maryland: The state added 22 more coronavirus cases, to the total of 63 cases.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|title=Coronavirus cases surge as Northam bans gatherings of more than 10, Hogan postpones primary|last=Chason|first=Rachel|date=18 March 2020|website=Washington Post|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318121502/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/maryland-virginia-dc-coronavirus-tuesday-updates/2020/03/17/5f6fa73c-684e-11ea-9923-57073adce27c_story.html|archive-date=March 18, 2020|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n*Michigan: The first death from coronavirus in the state is reported, a man in his 50s who had underlying medical conditions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clickondetroit.com/news/local/2020/03/18/man-at-wayne-county-hospital-is-michigans-first-confirmed-coronavirus-death/|title=Man at Wayne County hospital is Michigan's first confirmed coronavirus death|website=clickondetroit.com|access