869771.html|archive-date=March 21, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n*California: Beginning at 12:01 am on Tuesday, March 17, the counties of San Francisco, Marin, Santa Clara, Santa Cruz, San Mateo, Contra Costa, and Alameda, with a combined population of approximately 7 million people, are placed under a mandatory \"shelter in place\" order requiring everyone to stay home and all businesses to close except for those providing \"essential services\" (such as groceries, hospitals, pharmacies, banks, or delivery services), \"essential infrastructure\" (such as utilities or public transportation), or \"essential government functions\".<ref>{{cite news |last=Har |first=Janie |url=https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |title=San Francisco Bay Area counties issue shelter-in-place order |date=2020-03-16 |agency=Associated Press |access-date=March 18, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318024109/https://apnews.com/a342998638cdccb56172a1663e8d6edf |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Arango |first=Tim |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |title=To Battle Virus, 6 California Counties Order Everyone to Stay Home |date=2020-03-16 |work=The New York Times |access-date=2020-03-17 |last2=Fuller |first2=Thomas |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |last3=Eligon |first3=John |last4=Dougherty |first4=Conor |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318041903/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/16/us/california-covid-19.html |archive-date=March 18, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n*Florida: Governor of Florida announces it has 24 new cases, increasing the total to 216 cases.<ref name=\"Cutway\">{{cite web|url=https://www.clickorlando.com/news/local/2020/03/17/florida-coronavirus-cases-swells-to-216-governor-says/|title=Number of Florida coronavirus cases swells to 216, governor says|last=Cutway|first=Adrienne|date=2020-03-17|website=WKMG|language=en|access-date=2020-03-18|archive-url=https://web.