r violating the [[stay-at-home order]] that goes into effect at midnight. However, a major purpose of the order is to provide enforcement for businesses which are not complying.<ref>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ L.A. Mayor Promises 'People Aren't Going To Be Marched Into Jail' Under New Safer At Home Order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320200928/https://deadline.com/2020/03/los-angeles-mayor-shutdown-enforcement-order-eric-garcetti-lapd-1202888219/ |date=March 20, 2020 }}\" by Dominic Patten, ''Deadline'', March 20, 2020</ref> Marijuana dispensaries are classified \"essential\".<ref>[https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html Marijuana dispensaries are deemed 'essential' in LA, allowed to stay open during coronavirus order] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321025617/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/20/us/la-marijuana-coronavirus-trnd/index.html |date=March 21, 2020 }} By Allen Kim, CNN, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*Illinois: Governor [[J.B. Pritzker]] issued a stay-at-home order. The order will become effective March 21 and will remain in place until April 7 but could go longer.<ref>[https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/coronavirus-illinois-issue-stay-home-order-13-million-residents-california-n1164901?fbclid=IwAR0hnei6UFmSAf_aiG9deV6sjuK8LQqcB9T1s8mpqSQHe7WR3ILy0pluCZU Coronavirus: Illinois issues stay-at-home order for 13 million residents] By Minyvonne Burke, NBC News, 20 Mar 2020</ref>\n*New York: Governor [[Andrew Cuomo]] issued a state-wide order that all non-essential workers must stay at home. He noted that the number of coronavirus cases in the state had gone from zero on March 4 to over 2,900.<ref name=deadline>\"[https://deadline.com/2020/03/new-york-stay-at-home-order-andrew-cuomo-1202888587/ New York Governor Issues Statewide Stay-At-Home Order For All Non-Essential Workers] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.or